### 1. GET All Employees
# Roles: Manager, HR
GET https://localhost:8443/api/employees
Accept: application/json

---

### 2. GET Employee by ID
# Roles: Manager, HR
GET https://localhost:8443/api/employees/1
Accept: application/json

---

### 3. POST Create a New Employee
# Roles: HR Only
POST https://localhost:8443/api/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Johnson",
  "contractType": "Full-Time",
  "startDate": "2023-05-15",
  "salary": 55000.0,
  "email": "alice.johnson@example.com"
}

---

### 4. PUT Update an Employee
# Roles: HR Only
PUT https://localhost:8443/api/employees/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Johnson",
  "contractType": "Permanent",
  "startDate": "2023-05-15",
  "salary": 60000.0,
  "email": "alice.j.new@example.com"
}

---

### 5. DELETE an Employee
# Roles: HR Only
DELETE https://localhost:8443/api/employees/1

---

### 6. GET All Departments
# Roles: Manager, HR
# Note: URL is /api/api/departments because of the double mapping in your controller
GET https://localhost:8443/api/api/departments
Accept: application/json

---

### 7. POST Create a New Department
# Roles: HR Only
POST https://localhost:8443/api/api/departments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Logistics",
  "budget": 150000.0,
  "location": "Warehouse A"
}

---

### 8. POST Assign an Employee to a Department
# Roles: HR Only
POST https://localhost:8443/api/api/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "AssignmentTest",
  "accessLevel": "HighestLevel",
  "employeeId": 1,
  "departmentId": 1
}

---

### 9. DELETE an Assignment
# Roles: HR Only
DELETE https://localhost:8443/api/api/assignments/1

---

### 10. PUT Promote an Employee
# Roles: HR Only
# Note: No JSON body is needed for this endpoint as it only relies on the ID in the URL
PUT https://localhost:8443/api/api/employees/1/promote